{"key":"processedPost-10340710","value":{"id":10340710,"first":10340011,"last":10340710,"when":1242361599,"utime":"05/15/09 07:26 AM","content":"You lift the wax paper every time you fan, and then put it back on.&nbsp; The purpose of the wax paper is to hold a high humidity of near 100% right at the surface of the substrate/casing layer.<br /><br />Wax paper doesn't inhibit air exchange if you do it right.&nbsp; You're supposed to crumple it into a ball, and then flatten it back out again.&nbsp; All the wrinkles allow plenty of air to flow underneath.<br /><br />Replace with a fresh sheet when it gets damp or soggy, but at least every two or three days.&nbsp; Leave in place right through harvest if your grow area suffers from low humidity.&nbsp; The fruits will push it out of the way as they grow.<br />RR","title":"Re: when to remove wax paper"}}